>The Knights returned to the winner's list with an impressive win at Magic Round, while the Titans will be boosted by the return of Jayden Campbell. Newcastle ended a five-match losing streak with a dominant Magic Round 30-4 demolition of the Rabbitohs, breaking a losing run that started with a 26-6 defeat to the Titans in round 3. Gold Coast have now lost five straight, including a 20 point loss to the Bulldogs last weekend, and sit 16th on the ladder. Brisbane followed up a commanding win over ladder-leaders Canterbury with a deflating 32-8 loss to the Panthers. Ezra Mam’s nine-week suspension is over, but he returns via Queensland Cup.
